<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2016-02-29</DATELINE><TITLE>Deciphering MERS-CoV Evolution in Dromedary Camels</TITLE><BODY>The emergence of the Middle East respiratory syndrome coronavirus (MERS-CoV) poses a potential threat to global public health. Many aspects of the evolution and transmission of MERS-CoV in its animal reservoir remain unclear. A recent study provides new insights into the evolution and transmission of MERS-CoV in dromedary camels.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>